The paper uses deep reinforcement learning to analyze defensive strategies in the NBA, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis also involves trajectory data and outcome prediction, which could be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and statistical learning (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper presents a framework for understanding defensive strategies, which could be considered under social and information networks (cs.SI).
